Date:  0/0/2008
Source:  internet - see Notes
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  Co-founded by The Fifth Season and GABA, Heroic Gardens was started as a fund-raiser for Auckland City Mission's Herne Bay House, a respite and treatment centre for people living with HiV and AiDS. The festival has become an annual event ever since. Over the last eleven years Heroic Gardens Festival has given over $415,000 to two charities who assist those living with or affected by HiV.
Notes:  http://heroicgardens.org.nz/

Date:  0/0/2008
Source:  internet - see Notes
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  First held in 1997, Heroic Gardens is a yearly event which has become a much enjoyed part of the Auckland summer calendar. it appeals to a broad spectrum of the community and provides an opportunity to see a diverse range of gardens and to meet the garden owners.
Notes:  http://www.heroicgardens.org.nz/

